2. Price Elasticity Part One (Weighted Bumble Bee):

#Calculating Bumble Bee weights 
BBSWeight = sum(tuna$MOVE3)/sum(tuna$MOVE3,tuna$MOVE4,tuna$MOVE6)
BBCWeight = sum(tuna$MOVE4)/sum(tuna$MOVE3,tuna$MOVE4,tuna$MOVE6)
BBLWeight = sum(tuna$MOVE6)/sum(tuna$MOVE3,tuna$MOVE4,tuna$MOVE6)

BBPrice = tuna$LPRICE3*BBSWeight+tuna$LPRICE4*BBCWeight+tuna$LPRICE6*BBLWeight
BBMove = tuna$MOVE3*BBSWeight+tuna$MOVE4*BBCWeight+tuna$MOVE6*BBLWeight

#Brand 1: Star Kist

StarKistCPE = lm(log(MOVE1) ~ LPRICE1+LPRICE2+BBPrice+LPRICE5+LPRICE7,tuna)

4. Market Share (Weighted Bumble Bee):

#calculating geometric mean of sales for all 338 periods
geometric_mean <-vector()

for(i in 1:338) geometric_mean[i] <-exp(mean(log(as.numeric(tuna[i,2:8]))))

#calculating shares for brands
#Brand 1:
share.b1 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b1[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE1[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 2:
share.b2 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b2[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE2[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 3:
share.b3 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b3[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE3[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 4:
share.b4 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b4[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE4[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 5:
share.b5 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b5[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE5[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 6:
share.b6 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b6[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE6[i]/geometric_mean[i])

#Brand 7:
share.b7 <-vector()
for(i in 1:338) share.b7[i] <-log(tuna$MOVE7[i]/geometric_mean[i])

n = length(tuna$WEEK)
coef1 = 1-1/n
coefrest = -1/n

#Brand 1: Star Kist

Sk1 = coef1*tuna$LPRICE1
CoSRest = coefrest*tuna$LPRICE2
BBRest = coefrest*BBPrice
GeishaRest = coefrest*tuna$LPRICE5
HHRest = coefrest*tuna$LPRICE7

StarKistMS = lm(share.b1 ~ Sk1+CoSRest+BBRest+GeishaRest+HHRest,tuna)
summary(StarKistMS)
